<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[86275]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Lluís Soler makes his debut as director at the Sala Muntaner]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[Mercè Pons and Àlex Casanovas star in Pensaments Secrets, a play set around human relationships, fidelity and love.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Llorenç Rafecas and Lluís Soler have adopted David Lodge&#8217;s novel Think for the Catalan stage and are presenting it at the Sala Muntaner as Pensaments Secrets, starring Mercè Pons and Àlex Casanovas.</p>
<p>It involves a dialogue between Helen and Ralph. She is a widowed sculptor from a Catholic background while he is a philandering university lecturer. The action subtly unwinds thanks to several twists and turns, which also heightens the inevitable suspense that accompanies the audience up to the play&#8217;s final moment.</p>
